ATOI(3)                     Library Functions Manual                     ATOI(3)

NNAAMMEE
     aattooii, aattooii__ll – convert ASCII string to integer

LLIIBBRRAARRYY
     Standard C Library (libc, -lc)

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
     ##iinncclluuddee <<ssttddlliibb..hh>>

     _i_n_t
     aattooii(_c_o_n_s_t _c_h_a_r _*_s_t_r);

     ##iinncclluuddee <<xxllooccaallee..hh>>

     _i_n_t
     aattooii__ll(_c_o_n_s_t _c_h_a_r _*_s_t_r, _l_o_c_a_l_e___t _l_o_c);

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     The aattooii() function converts the initial portion of the string pointed to
     by _s_t_r to _i_n_t representation.

     It is equivalent to:

           (int)strtol(str, (char **)NULL, 10);

     While the aattooii() function uses the current locale, the aattooii__ll() function
     may be passed a locale directly. See xlocale(3) for more information.

IIMMPPLLEEMMEENNTTAATTIIOONN NNOOTTEESS
     The aattooii() and aattooii__ll() functions are thread-safe and async-cancel-safe.

     The ssttrrttooll() and ssttrrttooll__ll() functions are recommended instead of aattooii() and
     aattooii__ll() functions, especially in new code.

EERRRROORRSS
     The function aattooii() need not affect the value of _e_r_r_n_o on an error.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
     atof(3), atol(3), strtod(3), strtol(3), strtoul(3), xlocale(3)

SSTTAANNDDAARRDDSS
     The aattooii() function conforms to IEEE Std 1003.1-1990 (“POSIX.1”), ISO/IEC
     9899:1990 (“ISO C90”), and ISO/IEC 9899:1999 (“ISO C99”).

